import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['delay'] = pd.to_numeric(data['delay'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['delay'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.hist(data['delay'], bins=50, color='blue', alpha=0.7)
    ax.axvline(data['delay'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['delay'].mean():0.2f}")
    ax.axvline(data['delay'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['delay'].median():0.2f}")
    ax.set_xlabel('Delay Time (minutes)')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of delay time?')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['distance'] = pd.to_numeric(data['distance'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['distance'])]
    avg_distance = data['distance'].mean()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.axvline(avg_distance, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Distance: {avg_distance:.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    ax.set_xlabel('Distance')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count')
    ax.set_title('What is the average distance traveled by flights?')
    ax.hist(data['distance'], bins=50, color='b')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby(['origin', 'destination']).sum().reset_index()
    data = data.pivot('origin', 'destination', 'count')
    sns.heatmap(data, cmap='Blues', annot=True, fmt='d')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    plt.yticks(rotation=0)
    plt.xlabel('Destination')
    plt.ylabel('Origin')
    plt.title('Which origin and destination pairs have the highest number of flights?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data = data.sort_values(by='date')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.plot(data['date'], data['count'], color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count')
    ax.set_title('What is the trend in flight count over time?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.show()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['distance', 'origin']]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.boxplot([data[data['origin'] == origin]['distance'] for origin in data['origin'].unique()], labels=data['origin'].unique())
    ax.set_xlabel('Origin')
    ax.set_ylabel('Distance')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight distance by origin?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
